 popular in England during the Middle Ages, and strongly revived in the 19th century. It is most famous as the name of Dante's beloved, and is borne by the elder (  b. 1988 ) of the Duke of York's daughters."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":23,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Beatrice Archfield Blackmore was born in 1359, in Denchworth, Berkshire, England, her father, Baron of Archfield-Blackmore, was 32 and her mother, Baroness of Archefield, was 20. She married Henry Fettiplace in 1385, in Denchworth, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 3 daughters. She died about 1401, at the age of 43."},"et":{"1359–about 1401":"1359–umbes 1401","1359–1401":"1359–1401","1335–1411":"1335–1411","1385–Female":"1385–Surnud","1396–1494":"1396–1494","1397–1442":"1397–1442","1397–Female":"1397–Surnud","1398–1449":"1398–1449","1401–Female":"1401–Surnud","1327–Male":"1327–Surnud","1339–Female":"1339–Surnud","1385":"1385","1396":"1396","1494":"1494","1382":"1382","1327":"1327","1359":"1359","1335":"1335","1401":"1401","1411":"1411","1398":"1398","1442":"1442","1397":"1397","about 1401":"umbes 1401","about 1398":"umbes 1398","about 1385":"umbes 1385","about 1397":"umbes 1397","1339":"1339","1449":"1449","Great Shefford, Berkshire, England":"Great Shefford, Berkshire, England","Denchworth, Berkshire, England":"Denchworth, Berkshire, England"},"fi":{"1359–about 1401":"1359–noin 1401","1359–1401":"1359–1401","1335–1411":"1335–1411","1385–Female":"1385–Kuollut","1396–1494":"1396–1494","1397–1442":"1397–1442","139